  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.8.9`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nGet block by hash should return block information from an Ethereum node:\r\n\r\n    block, err := client.BlockByHash(ctx, blockHash)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nCalling Ethereum nodes other than `Geth` results in a response error:\r\n\r\n    block, err := client.BlockByHash(ctx, blockHash)\r\n\r\n    2018/05/30 02:44:55 missing required field 'mixHash' for Header\r\n    exit status 1\r\n\r\n#### Notes\r\n\r\nLooking at the Geth API documentation https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_getblockbyhash it seems that this field is not documented anywhere and also isn't implemented by alternative Ethereum implementations (e.g. Parity).\r\n\r\nAre there any ways around this issue without resorting to raw HTTP/JSON RPC requests?\r\nWhat was the reasoning behind relying on a custom response field for the block related methods?\r\n",
